Niger state government has relaxed restriction of movement of people from 2pm to 10pm instead of the earlier 10am to midnight. The restriction was put in place to check the rising case and spread of the Covid 19 pandemic sweeping across the globe. LEADERSHIP further reports that the state government has also directed Civil servants to resume work as from 8am to 2pm This is as the 12 entry point to the state is to remain closed. More Details Later…